GUIDED_DISCOVERY,❌,False,"""呃，老师，我看到导管口好像没啥特别明显的变化，可能有点水雾？氢气燃烧应该会生成水吧……不过我不太确定这些水会不会直接出来，还是都跑到空气里了。要是想收集产物，是不是得把导管插到烧杯里？不过我有点想直接看导管口的情况……因为感觉这样比较直观？""","[""Detach(object=match_1)""]",你刚才的想法很有道理，直接观察导管口确实能看到一些现象。不过，我们的目标是收集氢气燃烧后生成的水珠。你觉得水珠会自然留在导管口，还是会随着气体流动？如果我们希望这些水珠被收集到烧杯里，你认为是让导管口直接对着空气效果好，还是把导管插到烧杯里更容易收集到产物？你会怎么选择？为什么？,"You're on the right track! The products of hydrogen burning are likely to be water vapor and heat energy due to the exothermic nature of the reaction. Since water is a polar molecule, it tends to condense into drops when cooled or under high pressure such as in a burn bottle setup with an alcohol wick. This way you can collect some of these products by placing the delivery tube inside the beaker after the initial heating step which will help maintain the temperature required for continuous hydrogen production. After observing any changes at the end of this step, remember to check if there's any change in the environment that might affect your experiment like temperature or air flow. Now based on what we've discussed so far, how would you describe the overall process from start to finish?",0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,,"Skipped (strategy=GUIDED_DISCOVERY, not intervention)",8,690
