AFFIRM_AND_GUIDE,❌,False,"""老师，我觉得先加CuSO4！因为它是蓝色的，肯定一加进去就能看到颜色变化，比NaCl有意思多了。等下我就直接往试管里加点CuSO4溶液，应该会变蓝吧？""","[""Add(vessel=test_tube_1, reagent=CuSO4, unit=ml, volume=5.0ml)""]",你观察得很仔细！现在test_tube_1已经有了CuSO4和水。你觉得，如果我们想让离子反应发生，还需要加入哪一种溶液？你会选择NaCl，还是继续加水？为什么？,you're right! The solution in the test-tube will turn blue due to the presence of copper ions. Now let's move on to the next step and add sodium chloride solution. What do you expect to observe when you mix it with the blue solution?,15.92039800995025,8.040201005025127,15.92039800995025,2.1162145224826783,,"Skipped (strategy=AFFIRM_AND_GUIDE, not intervention)",8,940
