if one or more of the solutions caused a change in color or formed a precipitate, it would indicate the presence of a chemical reaction between certain ions. The nature of the reaction could be further inferred by observing the specific changes in color or the formation of a precipitate.",13.704496788008564,7.741935483870968,12.84796573875803,0.17346486905512726,,"Skipped (strategy=AFFIRM_AND_GUIDE, not intervention)",7,1094
